  "language": "en",
  "text": "Excuse me, sir. Question for you guys. How did you guys get rich? Who are you and why? I got a channel with 17 million followers. I traveled the world interviewing the richest people to help the younger generation. I've interviewed 25 billionaires in the last four years. What was your business? Private equity and venture capital. Actually, what was the most amount of money that you made in a single year? A lot. Give me a range. No. More than 10 million? Yes. More than 100 million? No. More than $50 million. Have you ever met a billionaire? Yes. What is the best advice you've ever been given from a billionaire? None. And I mean that. I had this conversation with my wife last night. 80% of people who are worth more than $25 million are miserable. Why? Did they just not ever get satisfied? God is money, and money is God, and that's all they work for. Are you happy? Happiest that I've ever been in my entire life. Why? I've filmed fulfillment. And you don't worship money? Don't give a flying fuck about it. Do you believe in God? Absolutely. When did you find God? In the last five years. In the last five years? At 50 plus years old. 60. Yeah. You look at what's happening in the world. A lot of shit's happening in the world. And at the end of the day, that's the most important thing because you never know when it's our day. I had a friend die today. Two friends died this week. Make every day the best. Have you ever been fucked over in business? Thousands of times. What did you learn from that? I will not do business with people who are not friends. If you're gonna be an asshole, I'm not gonna do business with you. Why do most businesses fail? Because they run out of money. Do you know why I think most businesses fail? No clue. I had a billionaire tell me one time that because they don't set themselves up for success from the start, I used a company called Busy to start my business to form my LLC and I turned it into a multi-million dollar business. And overnight, everybody thinks that it takes forever and it doesn't take that long, but I tell everyone when they're starting a business to use Busy to set up their LLC, that's all that matters. Your last message to the younger generation. I don't give a shit what your parents think. I don't give a shit what you're supposed to do. Go do whatever the fuck you wanna do. You got amazing advice there. It's so much for your time. I appreciate you. Absolutely. Did I get you contact? Sure.",
